Audience Blind Spots: No competitor explains that the American manicure requires shade-matching to your specific skin tone — that it is not one universal look, unlike the classic French. This is the most practically useful thing a reader could know and nobody says it.

Our Strategic Approach:

Differentiation: Frame this as a style identity decision, not a colour comparison. The real question isn't "which is prettier" — it's "which version of polished do you want to be?" Classic French = iconic, confident, statement. American = elevated naturalism, quiet luxury, skin-integrated. Give readers the tools to self-select with clarity.

Structure Plan: Open with what actually separates them visually (not a table — a real explanation). Then address the 2026 relevance question head-on. Then practical decision factors: skin tone, occasion, longevity/regrowth, DIY ease. Close with the 2026 verdict and the hybrid middle ground.

Tone Direction: Warm, direct editorial voice — the trusted friend who has had both done and knows exactly what to say to the nail tech.

